In this proclamation, President Donald J. Trump acknowledges the contributions of Americans of Asian and Pacific Islander descent to the development and diversity of the nation. He highlights the achievements of individuals such as Kalpana Chawla, the first woman of Indian descent to fly in space, and Susan Ahn Cuddy, the first Asian-American woman to join the U.S. Navy. The President emphasizes the shared values of hard work and commitment to ideals, and the importance of relationships with the Indo-Pacific region. He also encourages Americans to learn more about the heritage of Asian Americans and Pacific Islanders and to observe Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month in May.